[SN]TITLE[SN]
Aston rapist 'befriended' victim before hiding in her garden

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who befriended a student by carrying her shopping at a railway station has been jailed for seven years after hiding in her back garden and raping her.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Awais Khan, 26, of Witton Road, Aston, approached the woman after she had been shopping, and walked her home.
A week later he climbed over the fence, waited until his 20-year-old victim was alone and attacked her.
When released, Khan will be deported to Pakistan, he was told.
