At Birmingham Crown Court, Khan admitted two counts of rape and was sentenced to seven years and four months in prison. He will be on sex offenders' register for life.
Speaking after the hearing, Det Con Gavin McGrath, from West Midlands Police, said: "This young woman endured a sickening ordeal at the hands of Khan, who had planned his attack for a number of days.
"There are no excuses or grey areas when it comes to rape."
